results.description:
Meet PHP developers and entrepreneurs and discuss all topics related to PHP.

Typical evening lineup:

Our meetup starts at 6pm with people arriving and general chit chat about any topic people want, simply general networking. We have members of all experience levels attending, so there is usually someone with a similar interest for everyone.

Depending on speakers planned for the night, we usually start the formal part of the night at 7.00pm to 8:00pm. We have up to three speakers on any one meetup and topic will be announced in advance on the website and per email. There is usually time for general discussion after each presentation.

The evening ends at 9:00pm, when we have to vacate the building.

"Thanks again for your help finding someone to help me out. A. started work with me yesterday and it looks like it will work out well." - Chris
results.name: The Auckland PHP Meetup Group

results.description:
The Auckland Web Meetup is for creative professionals working in the web industry from designers, developers to business owners to project managers. 

We encourage any web professional to join this group and come along to our semi regular monthly meetings.  

Our meetings will always cover a variety of topics and have a break for food and beer in-between sessions.

results.description:

We generally alternate between having talks and hackfest evenings where you can bring along a project you are working on and get help.

results.description:
If you are a fan of anything sci-fi, fantasy, super hero or zombie related then this is the group for you! Our current and old school favourites include Dr Who, Game of Thrones, Star Trek, Star Wars, Walking Dead, Big Bang Theory, Hannibal, Firefly, Farscape, Stargate, Red Dwarf, Babylon 5 - you get the idea!,

Meetup events consist of getting together to watch scifi shows and movies, book club, quizzes, laser tag, board games etc where you can hang out and argue with other sci-fi fans about all kinds of nerdy stuff that other people just don't understand.

This group is for over 18s only.
results.name: Auckland Sci Fi

results.description:
Agile Auckland is a community for like-minded agile practitioners (and those interested) to gather in Auckland to explore all facets of agility, so that we can help New Zealand businesses maximise their return on IT investments.

We have regular get togethers throughout the year on agile topics and thinking using the Meetup website; a great way to keep in touch and allow people to know what's happening and join in on the fun.

All those interested in agile software development, agile project management, or any aspect of agile practices should join up and get involved. We would love to hear from your experiences using agile techniques - both good and bad.

results.description:
This is a community of developers who value and care about software development as a craft and want to learn, excel, and connect with other developers and be a part of the software craftsmanship movement.

Manifesto for Software Craftsmanship

As aspiring Software Craftsmen we are raising the bar of professional software development by practicing it and helping others learn the craft. Through this work we have come to value:

• Not only working software, but also well-crafted software

• Not only responding to change, but also steadily adding value

• Not only individuals and interactions, but also a community of professionals

• Not only customer collaboration, but also productive partnerships

That is, in pursuit of the items on the left we have found the items on the right to be indispensable.
results.name: Auckland Software Craftsmanship

results.description:
This group is focused on software architecture and project design. Properly done, they are reducing the overall technology, coding and project risk, while maximising the productivity of the team and allowing to bring projects in on time and within budget and quality.
Both software architecture and project design are hard core engineering tasks.
For all of us who are interested in the best practices of software engineering, you are more than welcome to join.

We have launched Software Architecture and Project Design communities in the following locations: 

Europe:   The Hague, Basel, Stockholm, Oslo

Australia: Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane 

New Zealand: Auckland

Singapore: Singapore
results.name: Software Architecture and Project Design Auckland
